Zahtjevimo da bismo zapisali $z$ u obliku $z = r(\cos \theta + i \sin \theta)$, gde $r$ je modul $z$ i $\theta$ je argument $z$. Kao prvo, imamo da je

\begin{align*}
r &= |z| \\
&= \sqrt{(2 + \sqrt{2})^2 + (-3 - 3 \sqrt{2})^2} \\
&= \sqrt{4 + 4 \sqrt{2} + 2 + 9 + 18 \sqrt{2} + 18} \\
&= \sqrt{33 + 22 \sqrt{2}} \\
&= \sqrt{11(3 + 2 \sqrt{2})} \\
&= \sqrt{11} \sqrt{3 + 2 \sqrt{2}} \\
&= \sqrt{11} \sqrt{(\sqrt{2} + 1)^2} \\
&= \sqrt{11} (\sqrt{2} + 1).
\end{align*}Ovaj put, imamo da je

\begin{align*}
\cos \theta &= \frac{2 + \sqrt{2}}{\sqrt{11} (\sqrt{2} + 1)} \\
&= \frac{2 + \sqrt{2}}{\sqrt{11} (\sqrt{2} + 1)} \cdot \frac{\sqrt{2} - 1}{\sqrt{2} - 1} \\
&= \frac{2 \sqrt{2} - 2 + 2 - \sqrt{2}}{\sqrt{11} (2 - 1)} \\
&= \frac{\sqrt{2}}{\sqrt{11}} \\
&= \sqrt{\frac{2}{11}},
\end{align*}i

\begin{align*}
\sin \theta &= \frac{-3 - 3 \sqrt{2}}{\sqrt{11} (\sqrt{2} + 1)} \\
&= \frac{-3 - 3 \sqrt{2}}{\sqrt{11} (\sqrt{2} + 1)} \cdot \frac{\sqrt{2} - 1}{\sqrt{2} - 1} \\
&= \frac{-3 \sqrt{2} + 3 - 6 + 3 \sqrt{2}}{\sqrt{11} (2 - 1)} \\
&= \frac{-3}{\sqrt{11}} \\
&= -\sqrt{\frac{3}{11}}.
\end{align*}Ovaj put, imamo da je

\begin{align*}
\theta &= \arctan \left( \frac{\sin \theta}{\cos \theta} \right) \\
&= \arctan \left( \frac{-\sqrt{3/11}}{\sqrt{2/11}} \right) \\
&= \arctan \left( -\sqrt{\frac{3}{2}} \right) \\
&= -\arctan \sqrt{\frac{3}{2}}.
\end{align*}Ovaj put, imamo da je

\begin{align*}
w &= z \cdot e^{i \frac{3 \pi}{4}} \\
&= r (\cos \theta + i \sin \theta) \cdot \left( \cos \frac{3 \pi}{4} + i \sin \frac{3 \pi}{4} \right) \\
&= r \left( \cos \theta \cos \frac{3 \pi}{4} - \sin \theta \sin \frac{3 \pi}{4} + i \left( \sin \theta \cos \frac{3 \pi}{4} + \cos \theta \sin \frac{3 \pi}{4} \right) \right) \\
&= r \left( \cos \left( \theta + \frac{3 \pi}{4} \right) + i \sin \left( \theta + \frac{3 \pi}{4} \right) \right) \\
&= \sqrt{11} (\sqrt{2} + 1) \left( \cos \left( -\arctan \sqrt{\frac{3}{2}} + \frac{3 \pi}{4} \right) + i \sin \left( -\arctan \sqrt{\frac{3}{2}} + \frac{3 \pi}{4} \right) \right).
\end{align*}Ovaj put, imamo da je

\begin{align*}
\cos \left( -\arctan \sqrt{\frac{3}{2}} + \frac{3 \pi}{4} \right) &= \cos \left( \frac{3 \pi}{4} - \arctan \sqrt{\frac{3}{2}} \right) \\
&= \cos \frac{3 \pi}{4} \cos \left( \arctan \sqrt{\frac{3}{2}} \right) + \sin \frac{3 \pi}{4} \sin \left( \arctan \sqrt{\frac{3}{2}} \right) \\
&= -\frac{1}{\sqrt{2}} \cdot \frac{1}{\sqrt{1 + \frac{3}{2}}} + \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}} \cdot \frac{\sqrt{\frac{3}{2}}}{\sqrt{1 + \frac{3}{2}}} \\
&= -\frac{1}{\sqrt{5}} + \frac{\sqrt{3}}{\sqrt{10}} \\
&= \frac{\sqrt{3} - \sqrt{2}}{\sqrt{10}},
\end{align*}i

\begin{align*}
\sin \left( -\arctan \sqrt{\frac{3}{2}} + \frac{3 \pi}{4} \right) &= \sin \left( \frac{3 \pi}{4} - \arctan \sqrt{\frac{3}{2}} \right) \\
&= \sin \frac{3 \pi}{4} \cos \left( \arctan \sqrt{\frac{3}{2}} \right) - \cos \frac{3 \pi}{4} \sin \left( \arctan \sqrt{\frac{3}{2}} \right) \\
&= \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}} \cdot \frac{1}{\sqrt{1 + \frac{3}{2}}} + \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}} \cdot \frac{\sqrt{\frac{3}{2}}}{\sqrt{1 + \frac{3}{2}}} \\
&= \frac{1}{\sqrt{5}} + \frac{\sqrt{3}}{\sqrt{10}} \\
&= \frac{\sqrt{2} + \sqrt{3}}{\sqrt{10}}.
\end{align*}Ovaj put, imamo da je

\begin{align*}
w &= \sqrt{11} (\sqrt{2} + 1) \left( \cos \left( -\arctan \sqrt{\frac{3}{2}} + \frac{3 \pi}{4} \right) + i \sin \left( -\arctan \sqrt{\frac{3}{2}} + \frac{3 \pi}{4} \right) \right) \\
&= \sqrt{11} (\sqrt{2} + 1) \left( \frac{\sqrt{3} - \sqrt{2}}{\sqrt{10}} + i \frac{\sqrt{2} + \sqrt{3}}{\sqrt{10}} \right) \\
&= \frac{\sqrt{11} (\sqrt{3} - \sqrt{2})}{\sqrt{10}} (\sqrt{2} + 1) + i \frac{\sqrt{11} (\sqrt{2} + \sqrt{3})}{\sqrt{10}} (\sqrt{2} + 1) \\
&= \frac{\sqrt{110} - \sqrt{66}}{10} (\sqrt{2} + 1) + i \frac{\sqrt{110} + \sqrt{66}}{10} (\sqrt{2} + 1) \\
&= \boxed{\frac{\sqrt{220} + \sqrt{110} - \sqrt{132} - \sqrt{66}}{10} + i \frac{\sqrt{220} + \sqrt{110} + \sqrt{66} + \sqrt{66}}{10}}.
\end{align*}

A regular $n$-gon has $n$ sides, so it has $n$ vertices.  If we rotate the $n$-gon by $360^\circ/n$ degrees, we will get back to the original position.  The smallest positive integer $k$ such that $360^\circ/n$ divides $360^\circ/k$ is $n$.  Therefore, the answer is $\boxed{n}$.

U pravokutnom trokutu imamo $\sin A = \frac{a}{c}$ in $\cos A = \frac{b}{c}$, kjer $a$ je kat kota $A$, $b$ je kat kota $B$ in $c$ je kat kota $C$. V tem primeru je $b = 90^\circ$, kar pomeni, da je $\cos A = \frac{90^\circ}{c} = 0$. V tem primeru je $\sin A = \frac{a}{c} = 2\cdot 0 = 0$. V tem primeru je kat kota $A$ enak $0^\circ$, kar pomeni, da je $\tan A = \frac{a}{b} = \frac{0}{90^\circ} = \boxed{0}$.

Za vertikalne asimptote imamo da pravilno riješiti jednadžbu $x^2-5x-14=0$. Ova je kvadratna jednadžba, a ona ima dva rešenja, odnosno dva rešenja, odnosno dva vertikalna asimptota. Ovi rešenja izračunat ćemo s pomoću kvadratne formula: $x_{1,2}=\frac{-b\pm\sqrt{b^2-4ac}}{2a}=\frac{5\pm\sqrt{25+56}}{2}=\frac{5\pm9}{2}$. Ova dva rešenja su $x_1=-2$ i $x_2=7$. Sada imamo da je $a+b=-2+7=5$. Ovaj izraz možemo zapisati kao $f(x)=\frac{2x}{(x-7)(x+2)}$. Ovo je oblik nekih ovačina, a onda možemo da izračunemo horizontalnu asimptotu. Ova asimptota je $y=c=0$, jer imamo da je $\lim\limits_{x\to\infty}\frac{2x}{(x-7)(x+2)}=0$. Sada imamo da je $a+b+c=5+0=\boxed{5}$.

\begin{align*}
\frac{\sec x}{\sin x} - \frac{\sin x}{\cos x} &= \frac{1/\cos x}{\sin x} - \frac{\sin x}{\cos x} \\
&= \frac{1}{\cos x \sin x} - \frac{\sin x}{\cos x} \\
&= \frac{1 - \sin^2 x}{\cos x \sin x} \\
&= \frac{\cos^2 x}{\cos x \sin x} \\
&= \frac{\cos x}{\sin x} \\
&= \boxed{\cot x}.
\end{align*}

The product of $3t^2+5t+a$ and $4t^2+bt-2$ is \begin{align*}
&12t^4+3bt^3-6t^2\\
&+20t^3+5bt^2-10t\\
&+4at^2+abt-2a\\
&=12t^4+(3b+20)t^3+(5b+4a-6)t^2+(ab-10)t-2a.
\end{align*}We know that this is equal to $12t^4+26t^3-8t^2-16t+6$.  Therefore, we must have \begin{align*}
3b+20&=26,\\
5b+4a-6&=-8,\\
ab-10&=-16,\\
-2a&=6.
\end{align*}From the last equation, $a=-3$.  Substituting this into the third equation, we get $-3b=-16+10=-6$, so $b=2$.  Therefore, $a+b=-3+2=\boxed{-1}$.

Kružnica ima oblik $(x-a)^2+(y-b)^2=r^2$ gdje je $(a,b)$ centar kružnice i $r$ radijus. Uzmimo da je centar kružnice $(5, -3)$, jer onda je $a = \frac{10}{2}$ i $b = \frac{-6}{2}$. Kada radijus kružnice iznosi 1, onda je $r=1$. Uvrstimo to u oblik kružnice i izračunajmo $c$: \begin{align*}
(x-a)^2+(y-b)^2&=r^2\\
(x-5)^2+(y+3)^2&=1^2\\
x^2-10x+25+y^2+6y+9&=1\\
x^2-10x+y^2+6y+33&=1\\
x^2-10x+y^2+6y+32&=0

We can write the numerator as
\begin{align*}
&\cos 5^\circ \cos 20^\circ + \cos 35^\circ \cos 50^\circ - \sin 5^\circ \sin 20^\circ - \sin 35^\circ \sin 50^\circ \\
&= \cos 5^\circ \cos 20^\circ - \sin 5^\circ \sin 20^\circ + \cos 35^\circ \cos 50^\circ - \sin 35^\circ \sin 50^\circ \\
&= \cos (5^\circ + 20^\circ) + \cos (35^\circ + 50^\circ) \\
&= \cos 25^\circ + \cos 85^\circ \\
&= \cos 25^\circ + \sin 5^\circ.
\end{align*}Similarly, we can write the denominator as
\begin{align*}
&\sin 5^\circ \cos 20^\circ - \sin 35^\circ \cos 50^\circ + \cos 5^\circ \sin 20^\circ - \cos 35^\circ \sin 50^\circ \\
&= \sin 5^\circ \cos 20^\circ + \cos 5^\circ \sin 20^\circ - \sin 35^\circ \cos 50^\circ - \cos 35^\circ \sin 50^\circ \\
&= \sin (5^\circ + 20^\circ) - \sin (35^\circ + 50^\circ) \\
&= \sin 25^\circ - \sin 85^\circ \\
&= \sin 25^\circ - \cos 5^\circ.
\end{align*}Therefore,
\[\tan \theta = \frac{\cos 25^\circ + \sin 5^\circ}{\sin 25^\circ - \cos 5^\circ}.\]Let $x = \tan 5^\circ.$  Then
\begin{align*}
\tan \theta &= \frac{\cos 25^\circ + \sin 5^\circ}{\sin 25^\circ - \cos 5^\circ} \\
&= \frac{\cos 25^\circ + \frac{x}{\sqrt{1 + x^2}}}{\sin 25^\circ - \frac{1}{\sqrt{1 + x^2}}} \\
&= \frac{\cos 25^\circ \sqrt{1 + x^2} + x}{\sin 25^\circ \sqrt{1 + x^2} - 1} \\
&= \frac{\cos 25^\circ \sqrt{1 + x^2} + x}{\sin 25^\circ \sqrt{1 + x^2} - 1} \cdot \frac{\cos 25^\circ \sqrt{1 + x^2} - x}{\cos 25^\circ \sqrt{1 + x^2} - x} \\
&= \frac{\cos^2 25^\circ (1 + x^2) - x^2}{\sin 25^\circ \cos 25^\circ (1 + x^2) - x \cos 25^\circ \sqrt{1 + x^2}} \\
&= \frac{\cos^2 25^\circ}{\sin 25^\circ \cos 25^\circ - x \cos 25^\circ \sqrt{1 + x^2}} \\
&= \frac{\cos 25^\circ}{\sin 25^\circ - x \sqrt{1 + x^2}} \\
&= \frac{\cos 25^\circ}{\sin 25^\circ - \tan 5^\circ \sqrt{1 + \tan^2 5^\circ}} \\
&= \frac{\cos 25^\circ}{\sin 25^\circ - \sin 5^\circ} \\
&= \frac{\cos 25^\circ}{\sin 20^\circ}.
\end{align*}Thus, $\theta = \boxed{65^\circ}.$

Za $-1 \le x,$ $y \le 1,$

\[0 \le 1 - x^2 \le 1\]i
\[0 \le \sqrt{1 - x^2} \le 1.\]Ovde se možemo pretpostaviti da je $x = \cos \theta$ i $y = \sin \theta$ za neki $\theta$ iz intervala $[0, \pi].$  Tada

&= \cos \theta \sqrt{1 - \sin^2 \theta} + \sin \theta \sqrt{1 - \cos^2 \theta} \\
&= \cos^2 \theta + \sin^2 \theta \\
&= 1.

Površina paralelograma $OACB$ je determinantu matrice

\[\begin{vmatrix} 1 & -3 \\ 2 & -2 \\ 3 & 1 \end{vmatrix} = 1 \cdot \begin{vmatrix} -2 & 1 \\ -2 & 1 \end{vmatrix} - (-3) \cdot \begin{vmatrix} 2 & 1 \\ 3 & 1 \end{vmatrix} + 3 \cdot \begin{vmatrix} 2 & -2 \\ 3 & -2 \end{vmatrix} = 0 + 3 \cdot (-1) + 3 \cdot 2 = 3.\]

Ova jednačina ima dva rešenja. Neka je $z = x + yi,$ gdje je $x$ i $y$ realni brojevi. Tada je
\[z + \frac{1}{z} = x + yi + \frac{1}{x + yi} = x + yi + \frac{x - yi}{x^2 + y^2} = \frac{x(x^2 + y^2 + 1) + y^2 i}{x^2 + y^2}.\]Odatle sledi da je
\[\frac{x(x^2 + y^2 + 1) + y^2 i}{x^2 + y^2} = \frac{1 + \sqrt{5}}{2}.\]Zbog toga je
\[\frac{x(x^2 + y^2 + 1)}{x^2 + y^2} = \frac{1 + \sqrt{5}}{2} \quad \text{ i } \quad \frac{y^2}{x^2 + y^2} = 0.\]Zbog toga je $y = 0$ i
\[x(x^2 + 1) = \frac{1 + \sqrt{5}}{2} (x^2 + 1).\]Odatle sledi da je
\[x^3 - \frac{1 + \sqrt{5}}{2} x^2 + x - \frac{1 + \sqrt{5}}{2} = 0.\]Ovaj polinom ima trinom $x^2 - \frac{1 + \sqrt{5}}{2} x + 1$ kao delilac. U polici s misterijom su bila 8 knjiga, a u polici s matematikom 10 knjiga, a u polici s znanostima 6 knjiga, zato je bilo bilo $8+10+6=24$ knjige.
S obzirom da su s svake police smanjene dvije knjige, onda su smanjene ukupno $2\cdot3=6$ knjiga.
Sveta je smanjila ukupno $24-6=18$ knjiga.
U polici s matematikom su bila bila $10-2=8$ knjiga.
Sveta je smanjila u polici s matematikom $\frac{8}{18}=\boxed{\frac{4}{9}}$ knjiga.

Let $a$ be the first term and $d$ be the common difference.  We have \begin{align*}
a+3d&=200,\\
a+7d&=500.

The first six prime numbers are 2, 3, 5, 7, 11, and 13. The sum of these numbers is 41, which is odd. Therefore, the sum of any two of these numbers is even if and only if the two numbers are both odd. There are $\binom{6}{2} = 15$ ways to choose two numbers from the six, and $\binom{3}{2} = 3$ ways to choose two odd numbers from the three odd numbers. Therefore, the probability that the sum of the two numbers is even is $\frac{3}{15} = \boxed{\frac{1}{5}}$.

U ovom slučaju, vektor $\mathbf{a} \times \mathbf{b}$ ima dužinu $\|\mathbf{a} \times \mathbf{b}\| = \sqrt{3^2 + 2^2 + 6^2} = 7.$ Ovo je i $\|\mathbf{a}\| \|\mathbf{b}\| \sin \theta = 2 \cdot 7 \sin \theta.$

Svakorazneje, $\sin \theta = \frac{1}{2},$ pa je mogućan kut između vektora $\mathbf{a}$ i $\mathbf{b}$ jedan od vrednosti $30^\circ$ i $150^\circ.$

The condition $t+2$ is the inverse of $t$ modulo $23$ is equivalent to $t(t+2) \equiv 1 \pmod{23}$, which is equivalent to $t^2 + 2t - 1 \equiv 0 \pmod{23}$.  This quadratic factors as $(t+1)^2 \equiv 2 \pmod{23}$, so $t+1$ is a square root of $2$ modulo $23$.  Since $23 \equiv 3 \pmod{4}$, we know that $2$ is a quadratic residue modulo $23$.  We can find a square root of $2$ modulo $23$ by trying out different values of $x$ until we find one that works.  We find that $x=11$ works, since $11^2 = 121 \equiv 2 \pmod{23}$.  Therefore, $t+1 \equiv \pm 11 \pmod{23}$, so $t \equiv -1 \pm 11 \pmod{23}$.  The only value of $t$ that satisfies $0 < t < 23$ is $t = \boxed{10}$.

Da bismo ga izračunali, potrebno je da izračunemo $\mathbf{b} \times \mathbf{c}$ i $\mathbf{a} \times \mathbf{b}.$

Koristeći da je $\mathbf{a} \times \mathbf{b} = -(\mathbf{b} \times \mathbf{a}),$ sledi da je
\[\mathbf{a} \times \mathbf{b} = \begin{pmatrix} 6 \\ -7 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix} = -\begin{pmatrix} -6 \\ 7 \\ -3 \end{pmatrix} = -\mathbf{b} \times \mathbf{a}.\]Odatle sledi da je
\[\mathbf{b} \times \mathbf{a} = \begin{pmatrix} 6 \\ -7 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix}.\]Slično, da je
\[\mathbf{a} \times \mathbf{c} = -\mathbf{c} \times \mathbf{a} = \begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 7 \\ 2 \end{pmatrix},\]odakle sledi da je
\[\mathbf{c} \times \mathbf{a} = \begin{pmatrix} -4 \\ -7 \\ -2 \end{pmatrix}.\]Sada imamo da izračunemo
\begin{align*}
2 \mathbf{b} \times 3 \mathbf{c} + 2 \mathbf{b} \times \mathbf{a} - \mathbf{a} \times 3 \mathbf{c} - \mathbf{a} \times \mathbf{a} &= 6 \mathbf{b} \times \mathbf{c} + 2 \mathbf{b} \times \mathbf{a} - 3 \mathbf{a} \times \mathbf{c} - \mathbf{a} \times \mathbf{a} \\
&= 6 \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ -7 \\ 18 \end{pmatrix} + 2 \begin{pmatrix} 6 \\ -7 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix} - 3 \begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 7 \\ 2 \end{pmatrix} - \mathbf{0} \\
&= \boxed{\begin{pmatrix} 12 \\ -81 \\ 90 \end{pmatrix}}.
\end{align*}

Osim toga, možemo dobiti kombinacije koja nisu dovoljne, tj. kombinacije u kojima su svaki član od svake stranke. Ova kombinacija možemo dobiti na $\binom{8}{5}$ način. Sredje kombinacije možemo dobiti na $\binom{6}{5}$ način. Ovo znači da možemo dobiti dovoljne kombinacije na $\binom{11}{5}-\binom{8}{5}-\binom{6}{5}=\boxed{436}$ načina.

Let the three consecutive integers be $n-1$, $n$, and $n+1$. Their product is $(n-1)n(n+1)=120$. Their arithmetic mean is $\frac{(n-1)+n+(n+1)}{3}=n$, so their product divided by their arithmetic mean is $\frac{(n-1)n(n+1)}{n}=120/24=5$. Thus, $n=5$, so the three integers are $4$, $5$, and $6$, and the largest of these is $\boxed{6}$.

Kvadriranje oba strana jednačine daje $x^2 - 4x + 4 = 16^3 = 4096$. Ovo je isto kao $(x-2)^2 = 4096$. Ovo ima dva rešenja: $x-2 = 64$ i $x-2 = -64$. Rešenje $x = 66$ ne možemo dobiti, jer ne postoji pozitivna vrijednost $x$ za koju je $\sqrt[3]{x^2 - 4x + 4} = 16$. Rešenje $x = -62$ je rešenje. Ovo je rešenje. $\boxed{-62}$

We have that
\begin{align*}
\cos \left( \frac{16 \pi}{15} \right) &= \cos \left( \pi + \frac{\pi}{15} \right) \\
&= -\cos \left( \frac{\pi}{15} \right).
\end{align*}Also,
\begin{align*}
\cos \left( \frac{8 \pi}{15} \right) &= \cos \left( \pi - \frac{7 \pi}{15} \right) \\
&= -\cos \left( \frac{7 \pi}{15} \right) \\
&= -\cos \left( \pi - \frac{8 \pi}{15} \right) \\
&= -\cos \left( \frac{8 \pi}{15} \right).
\end{align*}Therefore,
\begin{align*}
\cos \left( \frac{2 \pi}{15} \right) \cos \left( \frac{4 \pi}{15} \right) \cos \left( \frac{8 \pi}{15} \right) \cos \left( \frac{16 \pi}{15} \right) &= \cos \left( \frac{2 \pi}{15} \right) \cos \left( \frac{4 \pi}{15} \right) \cos \left( \frac{8 \pi}{15} \right) \left( -\cos \left( \frac{8 \pi}{15} \right) \right) \\
&= -\cos \left( \frac{2 \pi}{15} \right) \cos \left( \frac{4 \pi}{15} \right) \cos^2 \left( \frac{8 \pi}{15} \right).
\end{align*}We can use the identity
\[\cos x \cos 2x \cos 4x = \frac{\sin 8x}{8 \sin x}.\]Setting $x = \frac{\pi}{15},$ we get
\[\cos \left( \frac{\pi}{15} \right) \cos \left( \frac{2 \pi}{15} \right) \cos \left( \frac{4 \pi}{15} \right) = \frac{\sin \left( \frac{8 \pi}{15} \right)}{8 \sin \left( \frac{\pi}{15} \right)}.\]Then
\begin{align*}
\cos \left( \frac{2 \pi}{15} \right) \cos \left( \frac{4 \pi}{15} \right) \cos^2 \left( \frac{8 \pi}{15} \right) &= \frac{\sin \left( \frac{8 \pi}{15} \right)}{8 \sin \left( \frac{\pi}{15} \right)} \cos \left( \frac{8 \pi}{15} \right) \\
&= \frac{\sin \left( \frac{8 \pi}{15} \right) \cos \left( \frac{8 \pi}{15} \right)}{8 \sin \left( \frac{\pi}{15} \right)} \\
&= \frac{\sin \left( \frac{16 \pi}{15} \right)}{16 \sin \left( \frac{\pi}{15} \right)} \\
&= \frac{-\sin \left( \frac{\pi}{15} \right)}{16 \sin \left( \frac{\pi}{15} \right)} \\
&= \boxed{-\frac{1}{16}}.
\end{align*}

Let $x^4+2x^3+2=0$ have roots $\alpha_1, \alpha_2, \alpha_3, \alpha_4$. Then, by Vieta's formulas, $\alpha_1\alpha_2\alpha_3\alpha_4 = -2$. Also, note that $\alpha_1\alpha_2\alpha_3\alpha_4 = (\alpha_1\alpha_2 + \alpha_3\alpha_4)(\alpha_3\alpha_4 + \alpha_1\alpha_2) - (\alpha_1\alpha_2\alpha_3 + \alpha_1\alpha_2\alpha_4)^2$. Thus, \[
(\alpha_1\alpha_2 + \alpha_3\alpha_4)(\alpha_3\alpha_4 + \alpha_1\alpha_2) - (\alpha_1\alpha_2\alpha_3 + \alpha_1\alpha_2\alpha_4)^2 = -8.
\]Let $a = \alpha_1\alpha_2 + \alpha_3\alpha_4$, $b = \alpha_1\alpha_3 + \alpha_2\alpha_4$, and $c = \alpha_1\alpha_4 + \alpha_2\alpha_3$. Then, $a+b+c = (\alpha_1\alpha_2 + \alpha_3\alpha_4) + (\alpha_1\alpha_3 + \alpha_2\alpha_4) + (\alpha_1\alpha_4 + \alpha_2\alpha_3) = (\alpha_1 + \alpha_2 + \alpha_3 + \alpha_4)^2 - (\alpha_1\alpha_2 + \alpha_1\alpha_3 + \alpha_1\alpha_4 + \alpha_2\alpha_3 + \alpha_2\alpha_4 + \alpha_3\alpha_4) = 0$. Also, $abc = (\alpha_1\alpha_2 + \alpha_3\alpha_4)(\alpha_1\alpha_3 + \alpha_2\alpha_4)(\alpha_1\alpha_4 + \alpha_2\alpha_3) = (\alpha_1\alpha_2\alpha_3 + \alpha_1\alpha_2\alpha_4)^2 + (\alpha_1\alpha_3\alpha_4)^2 + (\alpha_2\alpha_3\alpha_4)^2 - 2\alpha_1\alpha_2\alpha_3\alpha_4 = 4$. Thus, $a^3 + b^3 + c^3 - 3abc = (a+b+c)(a^2 + b^2 + c^2 - ab - ac - bc) = 0$. Thus, $a^3 + b^3 + c^3 = 3abc = 12$. Thus, $a^3 - 12 = -b^3 - c^3 = (b+c)(-b+c) = -a(a^2 - 2b - 2c) = -a^3 + 2a^2$. Thus, $2a^2 + a - 12 = 0$, which factors as $(a+2)(2a-6) = 0$. Thus, $a = -2$ or $a = 3$. If $a = -2$, then $b+c = 2$ and $bc = -4$. Thus, $b$ and $c$ are the roots of $x^2 - 2x - 4 = 0$, which has discriminant $20 > 0$. Thus, $b$ and $c$ are real, which is a contradiction. Thus, $a = \boxed{3}$.

Ako je 8 učenika postiglo 90 bodova, onda je znao 8*90=<<8*90=720>>720 bodova.
Ako je 2 učenika postiglo 100 bodova, onda je znao 2*100=<<2*100=200>>200 bodova.

Za $\omega \neq 1$ vrijedi
\[\omega^3 - 1 = 0 \Rightarrow (\omega - 1)(\omega^2 + \omega + 1) = 0.\]Ovaj izraz je ekvivalentan $\omega^2 + \omega + 1 = 0.$

Dakle,
\begin{align*}
\frac{1}{1 + \omega} + \frac{1}{1 + \omega^2} &= \frac{1 + \omega^2 + 1 + \omega}{(1 + \omega)(1 + \omega^2)} \\
&= \frac{2 + \omega + \omega^2}{1 + \omega + \omega^2 + \omega^3} \\
&= \frac{2 + \omega + \omega^2}{1 + \omega + \omega^2 + 1} \\
&= \frac{2 + \omega + \omega^2}{2 + \omega + \omega^2} \\
&= \boxed{1}.
\end{align*}
